Jan 23
Release Notes
Overview

This strategy combines Opening Range Breakout (ORB) with three confirmation filters designed to work together as a unified entry system. Each filter targets a specific type of false breakout that ORB alone cannot detect.

Why These Three Filters Together

Standard ORB triggers on any price cross of the opening range. The problem: many breakouts fail immediately. After testing various filter combinations, these three address distinct failure modes that often occur independently:

VWAP Filter catches counter-trend breakouts. A long breakout while price is below a falling VWAP means you're fighting the day's flow. This filter requires price above VWAP with positive slope for longs.

Volume Filter catches low-participation breakouts. A breakout on 500 contracts is just stop-hunting; one on 5,000 contracts has real interest behind it. This requires minimum volume on the setup bar.

Candle Strength Filter catches weak-momentum breakouts. A bar can spike above the ORB high but close near its low - sellers actually won despite the breakout. This requires the close to be in the top 30% of the bar's range for longs.

These filters are independent - a breakout can fail VWAP but pass volume, or pass both but fail candle strength. By requiring all three, the strategy only enters when trend, participation, and momentum align.

Entry Mechanism

Uses stop orders at the ORB level for precise entries. When filters pass, a stop order is placed; when price touches the ORB level, entry executes at that exact price rather than waiting for bar close.

Risk Management

Two modes available:

Fixed Points - Set exact TP/SL distances in points. Example: TP=20, SL=10 gives 2:1 reward-to-risk.

Breakout Candle - Stop at the breakout candle's low (longs) or high (shorts), TP calculated as a multiple of that risk. Adapts to volatility automatically.

Optional breakeven moves stop to entry when price reaches a percentage of TP.

Settings

Core: ORB Bars (default 3), Trading Session, Max Trades/Day
Risk: TP/SL Mode, Fixed Points values or R:R Ratio, Breakeven trigger
Filters: Each can be enabled/disabled with adjustable thresholds

Long-term results are poor with defaults. Published as a research framework - test and optimize for your market.

Limitations

Filters evaluate on the bar before breakout. Default settings lose money long-term. Thresholds need adjustment per instrument.

Disclaimer

Educational purposes only. Not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Test on paper before risking capital.
